===Notes on results===
Bush received 62,040,610 popular votes compared to Kerry's 59,028,444.

Because of a request by Ralph Nader, New Hampshire held a recount.
In New York, Bush obtained 2,806,993 votes on the Republican ticket and 155,574 on the Conservative ticket. Kerry obtained 4,180,755 votes on the Democratic ticket and 133,525 votes on the Working Families ticket. Nader obtained 84,247 votes on the Independence ticket, and 15,626 votes on the Peace and Justice ticket.

'''''Note also:''''' [http://www.fec.gov/pubrec/fe2004/federalelections2004.pdf Official Federal Election Commission Report], with the latest, most final, and complete vote totals available.

===Finance===
[[File:2004CampaignAttention.png|thumb|450px|These maps show the amount of attention given by the campaigns to the close states. At left, each waving hand represents a visit from a presidential or vice-presidential candidate during the final five weeks. At right, each dollar sign represents one million dollars spent on TV advertising by the campaigns during the same time period.]]

* [[George W. Bush]] (R) $367,227,801 / 62,040,610 = $5.92
* [[John Kerry]] (D) $326,236,288 / 59,028,444 = $5.53
* [[Ralph Nader]] (I) $4,566,037 / 465,650 = $9.81
* [[Michael Badnarik]] (L) $1,093,013 / 397,265 = $2.75
* [[Michael Peroutka]] (C) $729,087 / 143,630 = $5.08
* [[David Cobb]] (G) $493,723 / 119,859 = $4.12
* [[Walt Brown]] (SPUSA) $2,060 / 10,837 = $0.19

*(money spent/total votes=average spent per vote)

